Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a parallel algorithm for solving the multiple selection problem in the congested clique model.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with finding the k-th smallest element in a set of elements.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper involves finding specific ranks in a set of elements.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithm.
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper presents a deterministic algorithm for solving the multiple selection problem.
